title: Episcopal church says it won’t help resettle white South Africans granted refugee status
description: Church refuses White House directive, citing longstanding ‘commitment to racial justice and reconciliation’The Episcopal church’s migration service is refusing a directive from the federal government to help resettle white South Africans granted refugee status, citing the church’s longstanding “commitment to racial justice and reconciliation”.Presiding bishop Sean Rowe announced the step on Monday, shortly before 59 South Africans arrived at Dulles international airport outside Washington DC on a private charter plane and were greeted by a government delegation. Continue reading...
author: Associated Press

title: First group of white South Africans arrive in US after Trump grants refugee status
description: Trump stirs controversy by calling Afrikaners, minority descended from Dutch colonists, victims of a ‘genocide’US politics live – latest updatesThe first group of white South Africans granted refugee status by Donald Trump’s administration has arrived in the US, stirring controversy in South Africa as the US president declared the Afrikaners victims of a “genocide”.The Afrikaners, a minority descended from mainly Dutch colonists, were met at Dulles international airport outside Washington DC by US deputy secretary of state, Christopher Landau, and deputy secretary of homeland security, Troy Edgar, with many given US flags to wave. title: How Donald Trump plans to beat Big Pharma and cut drug costs by 80%: 'Going to pay the lowest price’
description: Donald Trump's executive order aims to drastically cut US prescription drug prices, aligning them with the lowest prices in developed nations. Pharmaceutical companies face a 30-day window to voluntarily comply or face potential regulatory actions. The order targets intermediaries and promotes drug importation from countries like Canada.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Mayoral candidate, three supporters shot dead during live-streamed shooting in Mexico
description: In Veracruz, Mexico, mayoral candidate Yesenia Lara Gutiérrez from the Morena party was fatally shot during a campaign event, resulting in four deaths and three injuries. The attack, captured on a live stream, prompted condemnation from state and federal leaders, who vowed to bring the perpetrators to justice.
